cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SE 

This paper is a critique of a platform for security analysis of deep learning models, which falls under the intersection of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically discusses the evaluation of attacks and defenses on deep learning models, which relates to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses statistical analysis and draws conclusions about the effectiveness of the platform, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE).
